{{italic title}} '''''Reelside''''' is a 2015 Canadian documentary television series about the creative process of Canadian filmmakers that premiered on [[The Movie Network]] on June 4, 2015.
''Reelside''<nowiki/>'s first season features: [[Sarah Gadon]] and [[Caitlin Cronenberg]], [[George A. Romero]], [[Seth Rogen]], [[Evan Goldberg]], and Matthew Bass, [[Vincenzo Natali]], [[Michael Hogan (Canadian actor)|Michael Hogan]], [[Graeme Manson]], [[Don McKellar]], [[Bruce McDonald (director)|Bruce McDonald]], Matthew Hannam, [[Stephen Amell]], [[David Hayter]], and [[Lloyd Kaufman]]. ''Reelside'' is produced by Fifth Ground Entertainment.<ref name="Broadcaster">{{cite news|url=http://www.broadcastermagazine.com/news/original-documentary-series-celebrating-canadian-filmmakers-premieres-june-4/1003649589/?&er=NA|title=Original Documentary Series Celebrating Canadian Filmmakers Premieres June 4|date=2 June 2015|work=Broadcaster|accessdate=5 June 2015}}</ref>
''Reelside'' marks the directorial debut of actress/model Sarah Gadon with her episode featuring her own creative relationship with photographer and frequent collaborator, Caitlin Cronenberg.<ref name="ctv.ca">{{cite news|url=http://www.etalk.ca/news/sarah-gadon-caitlin-cronenberg-reelside-directing|title=Sarah Gadon gives fashion and image-making an honest look in 'Reelside' directorial debut|date=4 June 2015|work=ctv|accessdate=5 June 2015}}</ref>
''Reelside'' has been nominated for two 2016 [[Canadian Screen Awards]] including Best Biography or Arts Documentary Program or Series and Best Direction in a Documentary or Factual Series for "Superheroes".<ref name="academy.ca">{{cite news|url=http://www.academy.ca/getmedia/6666f9ab-bd62-4568-89cd-6ad7671caf2e/CdnScreen16_NomineeList_TV_Jan2016.aspx|title=2016 Canadian Screen Awards Nominees List TV|date=19 January 2016|work=academy.ca|accessdate=19 January 2016}}{{dead link|date=April 2018 |bot=InternetArchiveBot |fix-attempted=yes }}</ref>
